// Baked reference-image data for the mountain splash scene.
//
// This is NOT procedurally generated — it's a real 24-bit RGB render of
// the reference mountain artwork (420x70, row-major, base64-encoded,
// decoded at runtime with Node's built-in Buffer — no extra dependency).
// Pixel-for-pixel identical to the original capture (same colors,
// gradient, scale) except for two symmetric edge fades that were part of
// a decorative border in the source capture, not the terrain itself:
// rows 0-2 (top) and rows 67-69 (bottom) are blanked to plain black.
// Nothing else is touched — mountainScene() in ui.js handles the mascot
// and the stars entirely on its own on top of this untouched terrain.
export const MOUNTAIN_GRID_W = 420;
export const MOUNTAIN_GRID_H = 70;
export const MOUNTAIN_GRID_B64 = '';
